The article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by President Donald Trump on July 21, 2017. The memorandum is titled "Continuation of U.S. Drug Interdiction Assistance to the Government of Colombia." It certifies that the interdiction of aircraft suspected of engaging in illicit drug trafficking in Colombia is necessary due to the threat it poses to the country's national security. The memorandum also states that Colombia has appropriate procedures in place to protect against innocent loss of life during such interdictions. The Secretary of State is instructed to publish this determination in the Federal Register and notify Congress.